extends portfolio_guide 

block content
    hr
    div.title="JW Mouse Highlighter - Python (2025)"
    div.subtitle
        #[a(href="https://github.com/jambalayadog/JWMouseHighlighter" target="_blank") JW Mouse Highlighter]
    div.portfolioTable
        div.portfolioTableRow
            div.portfolioContent
                div.portfolioContentImage
                    #[a(href="https://github.com/jambalayadog/JWMouseHighlighter" target="_blank") #[img.portfolioContentImage(src='../images/gameDesign/portfolio/JWMouseHighlighter_Preview.png')]]
            div.portfolioWriteUp
                li #[a(href="https://github.com/jambalayadog/JWMouseHighlighter" target="_blank") JW Mouse Highlighter]
                    ul.nested
                        li.nested Makes it easy to identify and follow the mouse without being obtrusive
                        li.nested Highlights the user's mouse with a circular highlight
                        li.nested Emphasizes the user's mouse clicks with a click marker
                        li.nested Customizable features; color, size, transparency, # of clicks, etc
                li I wrote my own version of this app because the version I was using didn't run in the system tray and couldn't be managed well
                    ul.nested
                        li.nested Built in Python using PyQt5
                        li.nested Has an Installer
                        li.nested Runs in System Tray
                        li.nested Can be set as Startup App
                li This project was completed over a couple of weekends
                    ul.nested 
                        li.nested Prototype on the first weekend, and refined on the second weekend
                        li.nested Anyone is free to build off of it!
    hr
    div.title="Wordle Project - Godot (2024)"
    div.subtitle="Infinite Wordle"
    div.portfolioTable
        div.portfolioTableRow
            div.portfolioContent
                div.portfolioContentImage
                    #[a(href="https://fantasyhockeycentral.com/game_helloWordle" target="_blank") #[img.portfolioContentImage(src='../images/gameDesign/portfolio/brave_MSZ0XOyfG1.png')]]
            div.portfolioWriteUp
                li #[a(href="https://fantasyhockeycentral.com/game_helloWordle" target="_blank") Infinite Wordle]
                li I made an infinite Wordle game because my mom loves Wordle and it was a good way to brush up on Godot.
                li This project took a couple of weeks to do.
                li This was made in Godot using gdscript, exported to html + webpack, and hosted on my server.
                li I reverse engineered a few features of Wordle, e.g. letter animation when guessing words, and made a few changes:
                    ul.nested 
                        li.nested Optimized features like the speed of analyzing guessed words
                        li.nested No daily limit, players can play forever
                        li.nested Reveal the answer when you don't get it
                        li.nested Added the ability to give up because sometimes no one wants to sit there stuck
                li There is a ton of Wordle projects out there, and lots of research has gone into word lists... Wordle now curates their word each day.
